    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-30T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-30T03:00:00-05:00" n="758"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d758">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.6336/11–3048: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-30T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 30, 1948—4 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 1—4:09 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1275. We have heard nothing from Mukden since Communists closed transmitter but
                    assume he has been attempting communicate with outside world. Since his efforts
                    apparently fruitless, Department may wish to instruct either Moscow or Dairen to
                    make an approach to Soviet authorities to ascertain his welfare.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
